# Grafana Frontend Conventions

Apply these when editing Grafana frontend code under `public/app/`.

## User-facing strings — always translate
Never hardcode display text. Wrap it with i18n.

```tsx
// BAD
<button>Run query</button>
// GOOD
<button>{t('explore.toolbar.run', 'Run query')}</button>
// With inline markup:
<Trans i18nKey="explore.toolbar.run">Run query</Trans>
```
When interpolating values that may contain `/` or other special chars, pass `interpolation: { escapeValue: false }`.

## Styling — useStyles2, theme tokens
```tsx
const styles = useStyles2(getStyles);
// const getStyles = (theme: GrafanaTheme2) => ({ wrap: css({ padding: theme.spacing(2) }) });
```
Use `theme.spacing`, `theme.colors`, etc. — no hardcoded px or hex, no inline `style={}`.

## Types — no `as` / `any`
Avoid `as SomeType` assertions and `any`. Narrow with type guards and the `in` operator (e.g. read an unknown prop via `'expr' in query`), not casts.

## Components & tests
- Function components with hooks (not class components).
- Tests use React Testing Library; query by role/text, not implementation details.
- Icons must use valid `IconName` values — invalid names log a warning and fail tests.
